title: For Sale:  500 rd Summit 5.56 77gr Sierra Match BTHP MK 262 - FREE SHIPPING
postcontent:
These are not your ordinary 5.56 rounds...

These are the rare MK 262 rounds used by US Special Operations for long-range stopping power (600 yards).

Item (In Sock): 500 rounds NEW (not reloads) Summit MK 262 5.56 77 grain Sierra MatchKing Boat Tail Hollow Point (BTHP) in new Lake City military brass with sealed primers.

Shipping: Free ground shipping to the 48 contiguous United States.

MK 262: From Wikipedia: 5.56×45mm NATO Improvements:

Recently, advances have been made in 5.56 mm ammunition. The US military has adopted for limited issue a 77-grain (5.0 g) "Match" bullet, type classified as the Mk 262.

The heavy, lightly constructed bullet fragments more violently at short range and also has a longer fragmentation range.

Originally designed for use in the Mk 12 SPR, the ammunition has found favor with special forces units who were seeking a more effective cartridge to fire from their M4A1 carbines.

Commercially available loadings using these heavier (and longer) bullets can be prohibitively expensive and cost much more than military surplus ammunition.

Performance of 5.56×45 mm military ammunition can generally be categorized as almost entirely dependent upon velocity in order to wound effectively. Heavy OTM bullets enhance soft tissue wounding ability at the expense of hard-target/barrier penetration.

Accuracy: This is match grade ammunition, which means it's highly accurate and consistent because it's manufactured with precise, low tolerances.

In addition, the MK 262 has the toughest accuracy specification of any small arms ammunition issued by the U.S. military and requires a 1:7 or 1:8 twist to stabilize the 77-grain OTM bullet.

Range: 600 yards+

Bullet: Sierra MatchKing 77 grain (heavy) Boat Tail Hollow Point (BTHP). A boat-tail hollow-point bullet is a match grade bullet design that uses the concept of a teardrop-like shape to give it a lower drag coefficient and make it produce less turbulence in its wake. Only the base of the bullet has a boat tail-like shape — the meplat is still pointed.

Brass: New Lake City 5.56x45mm MIL-SPEC, unfired, heavy duty brass with a Lake City headstamp (not polished/shiny like commercial brass). It is the same brass supplied to our fighting forces in Iraq and Afghanistan and offers outstanding performance in AR-15 type rifles.

Primer: Sealed

Packaging: 1 Master Pack (5x 100 round boxes). 

Availability: In Stock (Limited Supply) - Available for Immediate Delivery.

title: For Sale:  HK USP 45 Full size race gun project
postcontent:
Bought this gun a few years ago and wanted to get into speed shooting but just never finished this one. Made a 9mm Glock race gun instead since there are more parts readily available and plenty of ammo. Collected everything in the pictures over the course of the last 2 years. Hardly got a chance to shoot this that much. I've put fewer than 500 rounds through it and I've kept it more than maintained. The scope mount is an original HK part and is quite hard to find, also have extra screws for it. Also comes with a caliber conversion ported barrel for 400 Cor-bon and 30 rounds of 400 Cor-bon and 9 pieces of brass. I shot a magazine of 10 and lost 1 at the range, which sucks because this is rare ammo, unless you reload of course. Also comes with Streamlight UTL with batteries and an extra bulb, some 45 ACP brass from all the rounds I've shot, 250 rounds of Remington UMC, and 20 rounds of Federal Premium JHP, 6 magazines (4 standard ten round, and 2 original 12 round), I also have 2 extended length National Match 45 ACP barrels (only one has been used as a practice barrel.) Original box and papers included. Also, this is a variant 1 double/single action pistol, I have also had a match trigger and match hammer installed, as well as switch the safety from the right to the left side and I used an HK45 safety lever, which is slimmer and fits and operates perfect, original left hand safety included too, for you weird left handed people out there! I've put too much into this gun and really hate to see it go... but right now there are more important things. I prefer to deal local, preferably with fellow WA Arms Collectors or those who have their CPL, but I can ship through my local FFL to you, but you will have to pay actual shipping & your FFL fee. title: For Sale:  Brand New in Box Del-Ton Sport!
postcontent:
This rifle is BNIB and comes with one brand new D&H 30 round magazine.

You can read a review of this model here: GunBlast.com Review 

The DT Sport proved to be one hundred percent reliable, as expected. The carbine fed, fired, and ejected every cartridge perfectly. Accuracy was excellent, especially considering the mil-spec trigger. I do much better work with a match trigger, such as the Alexander or Timney, but this carbine is built for fighting, and the trigger is well-suited to that task. The AR-15 is a wonderful concept, and Del-Ton executes it very well. The Del-Ton rifles are built very well, and just because the DT Sport is one of the most affordable AR-15 carbines available, does not mean that it sacrifices on quality. The DT Sport has everything that you need, and nothing that you don’t. It performs as well as rifles costing three times the price, and buying a basic rifle such as this leaves a lot more cash to purchase a good optic, plenty of extra magazines, and ammunition. You can’t have too much ammunition. The stuff keeps well, needs no refrigeration, and several thousand rounds will fit neatly under your bed. Buy it while you still can.

Also spec info easily found here:

http://www.del-ton.com/DT_Sport_p/dtsport.htm

Thanks for looking!

title: For Sale:  WINCHESTER 1886 DELUXE 96%+ CONDITION.. OUTSTANDING RIFLE w/ spcl.ord 30" bbl. CODY LETTER
postcontent: From my personal collection I have an absolutely beautiful and extremely high condition Winchester Model 1886 Deluxe rifle chambered in a 38-56 caliber. Manufactured in 1891. If being a Deluxe model with 3X walnut wasn't rare enough, this one comes with a special order 30" long octagon barrel (26" standard). According to "The Winchester Book" written by George Madis, on guns before serial number 100,000, 1 of each 900 rifles had a longer than standard barrel, 1 of each 320 guns had special wood, 1 of each 400 guns had pistol grips and 1 of each 570 had checkering. Add all of these rare features on a gun of this high condition and you quite possibly could have a one of a kind rifle. This rifle comes with a letter from the Cody Firearms Museum confirming all features and originality. There were only approx. 159,990 Model 1886's manufactured between 1886 - 1935. As for condition, overall this rifle would rate 96% or better. The receiver retains nearly all of its original, very vibrant case coloring, with almost all of its original clear coating as well.
